{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Automatic classifiersWe use our annotated dataset to train and compare several popular LLMs based on BERT and BERT-like [8] transformers architecture: multilingual mBERT [8], XLM-RoBERTa [35], monolingual EstBERT [36] and Est-RoBERTa [37].",
    "We used the larger versions of the publicly available models with 512 tokens to fit longer sentences that were optimal for our setup.",
    "We used a Simple Transformers library in Python [38] for working with transformers.",
    "To find the best hyperparameters, we minimized the evaluation loss whilst choosing between different batch size, learning rate, epoch and warm up ratio.",
    "The best parameters were batch size 16, learning rate 5e-5, 2 epochs and warmup ratio 0.1 for EstBert, and 16, 5e-6, 5e, and 0.1 for XLM-RoBERTa."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Automatic classifiersWe use our annotated dataset to train and compare several popular LLMs based on BERT and BERT-like [8] transformers architecture: multilingual mBERT [8], XLM-RoBERTa [35], monolingual EstBERT [36] and Est-RoBERTa [37].",
    "We used a Simple Transformers library in Python [38] for working with transformers."
  ]
}